  "codeExamples": [],
  "content": "Create a consumer named `<consumername>` in the consumer group `<groupname>` of the stream that's stored at `<key>`.\n\nConsumers are also created automatically whenever an operation, such as [`XREADGROUP`](), references a consumer that doesn't exist.\nThis is valid for [`XREADGROUP`]() only when there is data in the stream.\n\n## Redis Software and Redis Cloud compatibility\n\n| Redis<br />Software | Redis<br />Cloud | <span style=\"min-width: 9em; display: table-cell\">Notes</span> |\n|:----------------------|:-----------------|:------|\n| <span title=\"Supported\">&#x2705; Standard</span><br /><span title=\"Supported\"><nobr>&#x2705; Active-Active</nobr></span> | <span title=\"Supported\">&#x2705; Standard</span><br /><span title=\"Supported\"><nobr>&#x2705; Active-Active</nobr></span> |  |\n\n## Return information\n\n{{< multitabs id=\"xgroup-createconsumer-return-info\" \n    tab1=\"RESP2\" \n    tab2=\"RESP3\" >}}\n\n[Integer reply](../../develop/reference/protocol-spec#integers): the number of created consumers, either 0 or 1.\n\n-tab-sep-\n\n[Integer reply](../../develop/reference/protocol-spec#integers): the number of created consumers, either 0 or 1.\n\n{{< /multitabs >}}",
  "example": null,
  "intro": "Create a consumer named `<consumername>` in the consumer group `<groupname>` of the stream that's stored at `<key>`.\n\nConsumers are also created automatically whenever an operation, such as [`XREADGROUP`](), references a consumer that doesn't exist.\nThis is valid for [`XREADGROUP`]() only when there is data in the stream.",
  "notes": [],
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Overview",
      "level": 1,
      "content": "Create a consumer named `<consumername>` in the consumer group `<groupname>` of the stream that's stored at `<key>`.\n\nConsumers are also created automatically whenever an operation, such as [`XREADGROUP`](), references a consumer that doesn't exist.\nThis is valid for [`XREADGROUP`]() only when there is data in the stream."
    },
    {
      "title": "Redis Software and Redis Cloud compatibility",
